warning[PG000]: Policy Guard could not resolve a baseline lockfile; policy widening cannot be audited
  --> .locus/lock.json:1
  - tried to read the baseline lockfile via `git show <baseline>:.locus/lock.json`
  - the baseline ref / file / git itself was unavailable; PG001-PG004/PG006 cannot compare against a baseline
  - without an audit, an agent could quietly widen policy and pass `--agent-strict`; PG000 makes that visible
  fix: ensure the workspace is a git repo with a reachable baseline ref (default chain: `origin/main` → `origin/master` → `main` → `master` → `HEAD~1`); pass `--baseline <ref>` to set explicitly. If this is the first commit before `.locus/lock.json` existed, pass `--allow-missing-policy-baseline` to explicitly accept the audit gap.

